"{\"uid\": \"citizen.co.za-sport-sascoc-39-athletes-sa-team-paris-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Home\\u00bbSport ByWesley Botton Chief sports journalist 4 minute read 15 May 2024 01:22 pm Tatjana Smith will lead the SA swimming team at the Olympic Games later this year.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"score\": 0.901131173431149, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Botton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\"}, {\"begin\": 120, \"end\": 122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0878247918855833e-42, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"4 minute\", \"from\": 51, \"to\": 59}, {\"ngram\": \"Tatjana Smith\", \"from\": 86, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 134, \"to\": 151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Picture: Anton Geyser/Gallo Images It is full steam ahead for South Africa's campaign at the Olympic Games, with the SA Sports Confederation and Olympic Committee (Sascoc) announcing the first group of athletes in the SA team.\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 402, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 190, \"end\": 196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geyser\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9139724872662222e-17, \"text\": \"Geyser\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geyser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geyser\"}, {\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\", \"score\": 0.9999992987821045, \"rank\": 3.823490898926229e-07, \"text\": \"Gallo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gallo_Record_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 238, \"end\": 250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.941960166779292e-19, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 293, \"end\": 295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0878247918855833e-42, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0878247918855833e-42, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Picture\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 182}, {\"ngram\": \"full steam\", \"from\": 216, \"to\": 226}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 281}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic Committee\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 337}, {\"ngram\": \"Sascoc\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 345}, {\"ngram\": \"the first group\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 385}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are still opportunities for athletes to qualify in various sports, including athletics and swimming, and final squads in team codes have not yet been revealed.\", \"from\": 404, \"to\": 569, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"opportunities\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 433}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 438, \"to\": 446}, {\"ngram\": \"various sports\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 487, \"to\": 496}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 501, \"to\": 509}, {\"ngram\": \"final squads\", \"from\": 515, \"to\": 527}, {\"ngram\": \"team codes\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, at the first of three team announcements held in Johannesburg yesterday, thenational Olympic committeeconfirmed that 39 athletes had already been selected in seven sports for the SA squad at the quadrennial showpiece in Paris.\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 629, \"end\": 641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5991095111646604e-20, \"text\": \"Johannesburg\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johannesburg\"}, {\"begin\": 759, \"end\": 761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0878247918855833e-42, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4485455570934389e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"three team announcements\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 620}, {\"ngram\": \"thenational Olympic\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"39 athletes\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"seven sports\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 750}, {\"ngram\": \"the quadrennial showpiece\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 796}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While there were no real surprises, Shaun Maswanganyi (200m) and Francois Prinsloo (discus throw) were missing from the track and field list, but both athletes qualified more recently than others and should be included in the next team announcement.\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 1057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 844, \"end\": 861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"score\": 0.9999968692872139, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaun Maswanganyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaun_Maswanganyi\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no real surprises\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 842}, {\"ngram\": \"Francois Prinsloo\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 890}, {\"ngram\": \"discus throw\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 904}, {\"ngram\": \"the track and field list\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"both athletes\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 967}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"the next team announcement\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1056}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And while the make-up of the full team was still unclear, Sascoc president Barry Hendricks said he was optimistic about the nation's medal chances in the French capital.\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1134, \"end\": 1139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"score\": 0.9997432747854131, \"rank\": 0.00025486788329448273, \"text\": \"Barry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\"}, {\"begin\": 1213, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7520276336979212, \"rank\": 0.3094262210968912, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the make-up\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1080}, {\"ngram\": \"the full team\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1097}, {\"ngram\": \"the nation's medal chances\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 39-member provisional team included the likes of in-form 100m sprinterAkani Simbine, 400m world record holderWayde van Niekerkand 200m breaststroke defending championTatjana Smith.\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1414, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 39-member provisional team\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1260}, {\"ngram\": \"the likes\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"form\", \"from\": 1286, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"400m\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"championTatjana Smith\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1413}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If we look at the recent results in athletics, the athletes are coming together and peaking at the right time, and if you look at the action in the swimming pool as well in Gqeberha the other day (at the SA Championships) I was quite excited with the results and times,\\\" Hendricks said.\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1590, \"end\": 1598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Elizabeth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gqeberha\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Elizabeth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_Elizabeth\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the recent results\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1449}, {\"ngram\": \"athletics\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1462}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1476}, {\"ngram\": \"the right time\", \"from\": 1512, \"to\": 1526}, {\"ngram\": \"the action\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1557}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimming pool\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"the SA Championships\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1637}, {\"ngram\": \"the results\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1685}, {\"ngram\": \"Hendricks\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1697}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Let us keep our fingers crossed for the men's rugby sevens team as well, who must still qualify.\\\"\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1803, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1710, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"our fingers\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1729}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's rugby\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1757}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sascoc, meanwhile, confirmed incentives for athletes and coaches at the Games, to be held in the French capital between 27 July and 11 August.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 0.7520276336979212, \"rank\": 0.3094262210968912, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sascoc\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1811}, {\"ngram\": \"incentives\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1844}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"coaches\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1869}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1873, \"to\": 1882}, {\"ngram\": \"27 July\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1932}, {\"ngram\": \"11 August\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1946}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold medallists would receive R400,000, silver medallists would get R200,000 and bronze medallists would earn R75,000.\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 2067, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gold medallists\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1964}, {\"ngram\": \"R400,000\", \"from\": 1979, \"to\": 1987}, {\"ngram\": \"silver medallists\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2006}, {\"ngram\": \"R200,000\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze medallists\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2047}, {\"ngram\": \"R75,000\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2066}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their coaches would receive R100,000 for gold, R50,000 for silver and R25,000 for bronze.\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2158, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their coaches\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2082}, {\"ngram\": \"R100,000\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2114}, {\"ngram\": \"R50,000\", \"from\": 2116, \"to\": 2123}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2134}, {\"ngram\": \"R25,000\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 2151, \"to\": 2157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics Men: Pieter Coetz\\u00e9 (100m, 200m backstroke), Chad le Clos (100m butterfly), Matthew Sates (100m, 200m butterfly and 200m IM) Women: Aimee Canny (200m freestyle), Kaylene Corbett (200m breaststroke), Erin Gallagher (100m butterfly), Rebecca Meder (200m IM), Tatjana Smith (100m, 200m breaststroke), Julia Vincent (diving, 3m springboard) Athletics Men: Akani Simbine (100m), Luxolo Adams (200m), Benjamin Richardson (200m), Wayde van Niekerk (400m), Zakhiti Nene (400m), Lythe Pillay (400m), Tshepo Tshite (1500m), Adriaan Wildschutt (5000m, 10000m), Stephen Mokoka (marathon), Jovan van Vuuren (long jump) Women: Marione Fourie (100m hurdles), Prudence Sekgodiso (800m), Zeney Geldenhuys (400m hurdles), Rogail Joseph (400m hurdles), Gerda Steyn (marathon), Cian Oldknow (marathon), Irvette van Zyl (marathon) Canoeing Men: Andrew Birkett (kayak sprint), Hamish Lovemore (kayak sprint) Women: Tiffany Koch (kayak sprint), Esti Olivier (kayak sprint) Gymnastics Women: Caitlin Rooskrantz (artistic) Sport climbing Men: Joshua Bruyns (speed climbing), Mel Janse van Rensburg (lead & boulder) Women: Aniya Holder (speed climbing), Lauren Mukheiber (lead & boulder) Surfing Men: Matthew McGillivray, Jordy Smith Women: Sarah Ann Baum Wrestling Men: Steyn de Lange (92kg) Add The Citizen as a Preferred Source on Google and follow us on Google News to see more of our trusted reporting in Google News and Top Stories.\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 3599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2214, \"end\": 2226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chad le Clos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc